To seed you just leave the program you used to download it running (usually Vuze) with the file in the 'seed' queue and it does the rest. When you want to stop either close the program to stop it temporarily or remove it from the queue to stop it permanently. 
If you have already removed it then just reinsert it there.
Good luck

Reasoning for that:

Some video clips contain "DRM", which needs to be removed by installing a new "codec" for digital rights management or special player, which sometimes is actually a virus / malware / worm / personal info grabber / whatever...

I would be very careful, if the download site is not Microsoft, Apple, Sony or some really well recognised major music company. Personally I would never download any DRM codecs from never-heard small sites. Nor would I give any personal details there.

Internet is full of junk. And Internet if full of material encoded with all kind of strange codecs. Before downloading something, it pays to look for details, if any are available.
